Product Management Preparation Pathway

Step 1: Learn Core Product Documentation
Build a strong foundation by understanding and practicing:
PRDs (Product Requirement Documents)
OKRs (Objectives and Key Results)
RFCs (Request for Comments)

Step 2: Build a Product Portfolio
Create case studies that demonstrate:
Problem discovery
User research
Solution design
Prioritization and impact

Step 3: Teardown Global Products
Analyze well-known apps to understand:
User experience
Value proposition
Business model
Product decisions and trade-offs

Step 4: Improve Communication & Interview Follow-ups
Learn tools like Loom and Slack
After interviews, send a 2-minute Loom recap summarizing insights and next steps

Step 5: Use AI Effectively (Responsibly)
Use AI for first drafts
Analyze user feedback and product insights
Refine ideas, not replace thinking

Step 6: Job Search Strategy
Apply consistently through:
Wellfound
WeWorkRemotely
Remote OK
Himalayas.app


Salary Discussion Script
“I prefer to discuss market value rather than my current compensation. Based on my skills and the role expectations, I’m looking for a range between X and Y.”
